// Dev-only viewer wrapper -- NOT part of production ui/ sources.
// Gives the real ChatPanel a sane initial window size around it so
// slint-viewer (which has no --width/--height flag and no host to
// drive resize) doesn't render at its cramped natural minimum size.
// Uses preferred-width/preferred-height (initial-size hint only) rather
// than width/height (which Slint treats as a fixed, non-resizable
// window size) so the window stays freely resizable/maximizable via
// the window manager after launch.
// Imports the real app.slint unmodified, so --auto-reload still
// picks up edits to any production .slint file.
//
// Mock chat data below is set as plain property-override bindings
// (not --load-data JSON) -- --load-data only reflects properties
// declared directly on the loaded component, not ones inherited
// from ChatPanel, so JSON-driven mock data silently fails
// ("ignoring unknown property: threads" etc). Overriding via normal
// Slint inheritance (like width/height below) works because these
// bindings are compiled directly against DevRoot, same mechanism.
